# 📄 LLM-Powered Document Q&A System (RAG)

An advanced **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)** system that allows users to upload documents (PDF/DOCX) and **interact with them conversationally** using modern Large Language Models.

This project goes beyond basic RAG by supporting:

* 🔌 **Multi-LLM Providers (OpenAI, Cohere, Hugging Face)**
* ⚡ **Real-time streaming responses (ChatGPT-like UX)**
* 🎛 **Dynamic model selection per API key**
* 🧠 **Semantic retrieval with FAISS vector database**
* 💬 **Interactive chat interface via Streamlit**
* 🌐 Optional **FastAPI backend for API access**

---

## 🌐 Live Demo

👉 **Try it here:**
[https://rag-portfolio-zeta.vercel.app/](https://rag-portfolio-zeta.vercel.app/)

---

## ⚠️ Prerequisites

This project uses external LLM APIs. You must provide **your own API key**.

### 🔑 Supported Providers

* **OpenAI** → [https://platform.openai.com/api-keys](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)
* **Cohere** → [https://dashboard.cohere.com/api-keys](https://dashboard.cohere.com/api-keys)
* **Hugging Face** → [https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens](https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens)

> ⚠️ Without a valid API key, the system will not function.

---

## 🚀 Features

### 🧠 Core AI Features

* Upload **PDF/DOCX** documents
* Automatic text extraction & chunking
* Embedding generation (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`)
* Semantic search via **FAISS vector database**
* Context-aware Q&A using RAG

---

### 🤖 LLM Capabilities

* Multi-provider support:

  * OpenAI
  * Cohere
  * Hugging Face
* Dynamic **model discovery (top 5 relevant models)**
* Real-time **token streaming (not fake typing)**

---

### 💬 User Experience

* Chat-style interface (like ChatGPT)
* Streaming responses with cursor effect
* Model badges & provider indicators
* Source document references
* Persistent vector index (no reprocessing needed)

---

## 🏗 Project Structure

```
rag-qa/
│
├── app/                     # Core backend logic
│   ├── services.py          # LLM abstraction + RAG pipeline
│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app (optional)
│   ├── routes.py            # API endpoints
│   └── utils.py
│
├── dashboard/               # Streamlit frontend
│   └── app.py
│
├── vectorstore_index/       # Saved FAISS index
│
├── .env                     # API keys (local only)
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## 🧠 System Architecture

```
User
 ↓
Streamlit UI
 ↓
QASystem
 ↓
Retriever (FAISS)
 ↓
Relevant Chunks
 ↓
LLM (OpenAI / Cohere / HF)
 ↓
Streaming Response
```

---

## 🔄 Application Flow

### 1. 🔐 API Key Input

User enters API key for selected provider

### 2. 🤖 Model Discovery

System fetches **top 5 relevant models**

### 3. ⚙️ LLM Initialization

User selects model → system validates → ready

### 4. 📄 Document Upload

Upload PDF or DOCX

### 5. ✂️ Processing

* Split into chunks
* Generate embeddings
* Store in FAISS

### 6. 🔍 Query

User asks question

### 7. 🧠 Answer

* Retrieve relevant chunks
* Send to LLM
* **Stream response in real-time**

---

## ⚡ Streaming Architecture

### ❌ Before

Wait → Full response → Display

### ✅ Now

Real-time token streaming:

* **OpenAI** → `stream=True`
* **Cohere** → `chat_stream`
* **Hugging Face** → fallback simulation

