## ⚙️ Installation

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/emekaphilian/AI-ML-Projects.git
cd AI-ML-Projects
```

---

### 2. Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv .venv
```

Activate:

```bash
# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate

# macOS/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate
```

---

### 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

### 4. Set API Keys

Create `.env` file:

```
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key
COHERE_API_KEY=your_key
HF_API_TOKEN=your_token
```

---

### 5. (Optional) Set Default Provider

```
LLM_PROVIDER=openai
```

---

## 🖥️ Running the App

### ▶ Streamlit Dashboard

```bash
streamlit run dashboard/app.py
```

Open:

```
http://localhost:8501
```

---

### ⚙️ FastAPI Backend (Optional)

```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
```

Endpoints:

* `POST /upload`
* `GET /ask?q=...`

---

## 💾 Persisting FAISS Index

### Save

```python
vectorstore.save_local("vectorstore_index")
```

### Load

```python
FAISS.load_local("vectorstore_index", embeddings)
```

---

## ⚠️ Bottlenecks We Faced

### ❌ Fake Streaming

* Initially used character-by-character display
* Caused delayed UX

---

### ❌ API Inconsistencies

* OpenAI vs Cohere vs HF differences
* Required custom abstraction layer

---

### ❌ Hugging Face Overload

* Thousands of models returned
* Needed filtering logic

---

### ❌ UI Bug

* White text on white background

---

## 💡 Breakthroughs

### ✅ Real Streaming

* Implemented true token streaming
* Massive UX improvement

---

### ✅ LLM Abstraction Layer

```
BaseLLM → OpenAI / Cohere / HF
```

---

### ✅ Dynamic Model Selection

* User-specific model availability
* Based on API key

